- The Drifters – All‑Time Greatest Hits (Pop; Oldies; Doo‑Wop):
  - What we know: genre and era (oldies/doo‑wop/pop) imply short, hook‑driven songs and prominent lead vocals with backing harmonies. These recordings are typically centered on clear melodies and vocal hooks and were often arranged to showcase a front vocal supported by group harmonies and concise instrumental backing.
  - Match with preferences: aligns well with my liking for concise, hook‑driven tracks and supportive harmonies that color rather than compete; classic doo‑wop/pop arrangements tend to emphasize melody and ensemble cohesion rather than aggressive modern polish, which is closer to my preference for live‑take feel and band interplay.
